folder: 165th Street (West) & St. Nicholas Avenue, Manhattan, NY
text:
West 165th Street, south side, east from St. Nicholas to Amsterdam Aves., showing prominently in the center of this block the Roman Catholic Church and Rectory of St. Rose of Lima. The area in the foreground is locally known as McKenna Square.

April 8, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.
